WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

2
00:00:36.328 --> 00:00:39.665
{\an8}<i>Can one stone
change the course of history?</i>

3
00:00:41.125 --> 00:00:44.253
<i>Can one act of defiance
create a legend?</i>

4
00:00:46.088 --> 00:00:50.801
<i>I will tell you the story of
David. a simple shepherd boy.</i>

5
00:00:51.427 --> 00:00:52.553
<i>an outcast.</i>

6
00:00:53.053 --> 00:00:57.475
<i>who became one of the most
famous kings who ever lived.</i>

7
00:01:03.230 --> 00:01:06.108
<i>There was a time
Israel had no king.</i>

8
00:01:07.067 --> 00:01:10.738
<i>500 years after
Moses split the sea.</i>

9
00:01:11.447 --> 00:01:14.200
<i>the people were
leaderless and divided.</i>

10
00:01:16.285 --> 00:01:20.539
<i>So. Samuel. the last
of the great seers.</i>

11
00:01:21.165 --> 00:01:26.670
<i>anointed Saul of the tribe of
Benjamin as Israel's first king.</i>

12
00:01:27.338 --> 00:01:32.133
<i>But Samuel warned the people not to forget
the god that delivered them from Egypt.</i>

13
00:01:33.803 --> 00:01:37.639
<i>For 25
years. Saul has reigned.</i>

14
00:01:37.640 --> 00:01:42.561
<i>beloved by the people.
triumphant in every battle.</i>

15
00:01:44.063 --> 00:01:49.860
<i>As Saul's arrogance grows. a rift
between him and Samuel festers.</i>

16
00:01:51.028 --> 00:01:53.071
<i>With each new victory.</i>

17
00:01:53.072 --> 00:01:58.117
<i>the people of Israel trust more
in a throne than in their god.</i>

18
00:01:58.118 --> 00:02:02.330
<i>May the house
of Saul endure forever.</i>

19
00:02:02.331 --> 00:02:04.542
- Forever.
- Forever.

20
00:02:26.355 --> 00:02:27.772
How many are there?

21
00:02:27.773 --> 00:02:29.817
Upwards of 200.000.

22
00:02:52.172 --> 00:02:53.841
He's just a man. Father.

23
00:02:55.092 --> 00:02:56.092
Is he?

24
00:02:56.719 --> 00:03:00.222
How many days must we duress?

25
00:03:01.932 --> 00:03:03.851
Send me your champion!

26
00:03:06.061 --> 00:03:07.395
Cowards!

27
00:03:07.396 --> 00:03:10.316
All of you. cowards!

28
00:03:14.194 --> 00:03:15.571
Goliath!

29
00:03:27.499 --> 00:03:30.336
God
give me this ground.

30
00:03:31.128 --> 00:03:32.962
Every step. just one step.

31
00:03:32.963 --> 00:03:35.757
I ask for a champion!

32
00:03:35.758 --> 00:03:38.676
You come against
me with a stick?

33
00:03:38.677 --> 00:03:42.431
You will become the
victim of my wrath!

34
00:03:56.528 --> 00:03:58.154
Give me another.

35
00:04:03.827 --> 00:04:05.704
Another.

36
00:04:20.094 --> 00:04:21.387
No.

37
00:04:30.604 --> 00:04:36.068
<i>So. as the fate of
a people hangs in the balance.</i>

38
00:04:37.069 --> 00:04:39.488
<i>again I ask this question...</i>

39
00:04:43.242 --> 00:04:47.746
<i>can one stone change
the course of history?</i>

40
00:05:20.279 --> 00:05:21.405
What are you doing?

41
00:05:22.072 --> 00:05:25.951
That's better. It's
all right.

42
00:06:04.948 --> 00:06:07.242
Oh. no. Oh.

43
00:06:32.476 --> 00:06:34.436
All right. All right.

44
00:06:57.000 --> 00:06:59.378
Little
one. I'm so sorry.

45
00:07:02.506 --> 00:07:03.590
I've got you.

46
00:07:05.968 --> 00:07:08.762
Quiet now. Quiet.

47
00:07:23.735 --> 00:07:26.445
...you will
lead. This very land.

48
00:07:30.367 --> 00:07:33.828
Why could Moses not
go? Why did he have to die?

49
00:07:33.829 --> 00:07:36.998
Because when
he was very. very old...

50
00:07:36.999 --> 00:07:40.168
Like you?

51
00:07:40.169 --> 00:07:42.753
Yes. very old like me.

52
00:07:42.754 --> 00:07:49.178
Having led Israel 40 years.
Moses died on that mountain.

53
00:07:51.054 --> 00:07:54.141
Disobedience comes
at a cost. you see.

54
00:07:54.725 --> 00:07:57.728
Even for a great
one. like Moses.

55
00:07:59.354 --> 00:08:02.607
So what did
Joshua do without Moses?

56
00:08:02.608 --> 00:08:07.987
Well. God said to him three
times...

57
00:08:07.988 --> 00:08:14.535
"Be strong and courageous."
Do not fear. for fear is the enemy.

58
00:08:14.536 --> 00:08:15.661
You see?

59
00:08:15.662 --> 00:08:18.582
Fear is the thief.

60
00:08:19.625 --> 00:08:21.627
Then why must we still hide?

61
00:08:23.420 --> 00:08:25.464
Because his work is
not yet complete.

62
00:08:27.966 --> 00:08:29.593
That's right. David.

63
00:08:31.511 --> 00:08:32.971
So we must not fear.

64
00:08:35.057 --> 00:08:36.808
We must face fear.

65
00:08:37.476 --> 00:08:42.022
because God will always be
there on the other side waiting.

66
00:08:43.148 --> 00:08:45.691
Aren't you supposed to be minding
the sheep. little shepherd?

67
00:08:45.692 --> 00:08:46.777
I did.

68
00:08:47.527 --> 00:08:48.820
Not well enough.

69
00:08:49.780 --> 00:08:51.323
I saw what you brought home.

70
00:08:52.532 --> 00:08:53.741
The lion has returned.

71
00:08:53.742 --> 00:08:55.827
Oh. a lion. And where were you?

72
00:08:57.412 --> 00:08:58.455
Off...

73
00:09:00.249 --> 00:09:01.249
singing about your mother?

74
00:09:01.250 --> 00:09:03.334
Speak of my mother again.

75
00:09:03.335 --> 00:09:05.754
Nathaneel. David.

76
00:09:06.755 --> 00:09:09.090
Does the story of our
people mean nothing to you?

77
00:09:09.091 --> 00:09:10.634
Forgive us. Father.

78
00:09:12.010 --> 00:09:13.971
I was distracted
by the shepherd.

79
00:09:23.146 --> 00:09:24.314
Poor lamb.

80
00:09:24.940 --> 00:09:26.024
She survived.

81
00:09:27.484 --> 00:09:29.152
Does your Father
know you have that?

82
00:09:30.654 --> 00:09:32.571
Avva. go inside.

83
00:09:34.866 --> 00:09:37.286
- David.
- Father.

84
00:09:38.578 --> 00:09:39.913
How many did you lose?

85
00:09:42.082 --> 00:09:42.957
Four sheep.

86
00:09:42.958 --> 00:09:44.876
I'm not a rich man. David.

87
00:09:47.337 --> 00:09:48.422
It was the old king.

88
00:09:53.010 --> 00:09:54.177
That lion is dead.

89
00:09:55.178 --> 00:09:56.178
It was him.

90
00:09:56.179 --> 00:09:59.223
Until we truly kill him. the
sheep cannot graze there.

91
00:09:59.224 --> 00:10:00.516
We will lose more.

92
00:10:00.517 --> 00:10:04.520
David. you know I can
graze no other lands.

93
00:10:04.521 --> 00:10:06.398
Then let's gather some
men and hunt it down.

94
00:10:07.065 --> 00:10:08.775
- They wouldn't come.
- Why?

95
00:10:13.071 --> 00:10:14.071
Because of me.

96
00:10:14.072 --> 00:10:15.781
It is not because of you.

97
00:10:15.782 --> 00:10:17.582
All of Bethlehem
treats me like it is.

98
00:10:18.285 --> 00:10:19.703
Just as my brothers do.

99
00:10:20.412 --> 00:10:22.212
I'm nothing more than a
bastard in this house.

100
00:10:23.123 --> 00:10:25.667
You are my son. as they are.

101
00:10:27.794 --> 00:10:28.794
I will kill the lion.

102
00:10:29.212 --> 00:10:31.505
You will not.
I will take care of it.

103
00:10:31.506 --> 00:10:33.091
Like you did last time.

104
00:10:34.926 --> 00:10:36.678
I should've buried
that with your mother.

105
00:10:37.262 --> 00:10:39.847
I don't want to hear that
instrument in my house ever again.

106
00:10:39.848 --> 00:10:40.974
Heed my words. David.

107
00:10:42.392 --> 00:10:44.770
Father. this
is all I have left of her.

108
00:10:46.313 --> 00:10:48.230
- Where are you going?
- Where I belong.

109
00:10:48.231 --> 00:10:49.316
David.

110
00:10:50.233 --> 00:10:51.234
David!

111
00:11:17.803 --> 00:11:19.262
Show me your purpose.

112
00:11:20.180 --> 00:11:21.807
Show me your will for me.

113
00:11:23.141 --> 00:11:24.643
Show me who I am.

114
00:11:28.063 --> 00:11:29.064
Please.

115
00:11:53.255 --> 00:11:58.969
The song must be found and tended.
you know. like a living thing.

116
00:12:08.687 --> 00:12:09.771
Now you try.

117
00:14:03.677 --> 00:14:06.262
{\an8}<i>The last
great battle Israel would face</i>

118
00:14:06.263 --> 00:14:09.807
<i>before Goliath was
against the Amalekites.</i>

119
00:14:09.808 --> 00:14:15.146
<i>a brutal nation of blood drinkers who
had tormented Israel for generations.</i>

120
00:14:21.194 --> 00:14:24.947
<i>King Saul was instructed
by the great seer. Samuel.</i>

121
00:14:24.948 --> 00:14:27.157
<i>to keep no spoils of war.</i>

122
00:14:27.158 --> 00:14:31.287
<i>To take nothing from the
Amalekites and to slay their king.</i>

123
00:14:31.288 --> 00:14:33.205
<i>a vicious cannibal called Agag.</i>

124
00:14:39.045 --> 00:14:43.008
<i>After days of
fighting. my father. King Saul.</i>

125
00:14:43.925 --> 00:14:48.053
<i>and my brother. Jonathan.
were once again triumphant.</i>

126
00:14:48.054 --> 00:14:49.930
Victory!

127
00:14:52.058 --> 00:14:55.186
For God and for Israel!

128
00:14:56.980 --> 00:14:58.773
And for your king!

129
00:15:09.242 --> 00:15:10.744
My prince.

130
00:15:17.167 --> 00:15:19.044
The Lord has shined
upon us this day.

131
00:15:19.753 --> 00:15:21.211
How many did we lose?

132
00:15:21.212 --> 00:15:22.422
5.000.

133
00:15:24.966 --> 00:15:26.092
Heavy price to pay.

134
00:15:27.761 --> 00:15:29.638
But the Amalekites are defeated.

135
00:15:33.183 --> 00:15:35.601
We have news of a border village
destroyed north of Bethlehem.

136
00:15:35.602 --> 00:15:37.895
Border village? By who?

137
00:15:37.896 --> 00:15:40.857
I'm sending a scouting
party to find out.

138
00:15:41.816 --> 00:15:43.108
Get me a horse.

139
00:15:43.109 --> 00:15:44.861
My prince. it is
a full day's ride

140
00:15:45.487 --> 00:15:47.739
and you have been on the
field of battle for many days.

141
00:15:49.783 --> 00:15:51.034
Take me there.

142
00:15:54.746 --> 00:15:56.498
Let's go to the border village.

143
00:15:57.749 --> 00:15:59.041
Are you tired. Eliab?

144
00:15:59.042 --> 00:16:00.877
No. I am not tired.

145
00:16:14.808 --> 00:16:18.519
While we slay enemies on our right.
our people are attacked on our left.

146
00:16:18.520 --> 00:16:19.646
No defense.

147
00:16:20.230 --> 00:16:21.231
Unarmed.

148
00:16:23.525 --> 00:16:24.526
Who would do this?

149
00:16:25.777 --> 00:16:26.945
Philistines.

150
00:16:27.529 --> 00:16:29.405
Why so deep in our territory?

151
00:16:29.406 --> 00:16:31.408
There's nothing to gain here.

152
00:16:33.159 --> 00:16:35.495
Have any of you ever
seen anything like this?

153
00:16:36.121 --> 00:16:37.330
Eliab?

154
00:16:38.081 --> 00:16:40.521
They have been torn to pieces
without the kindness of a blade.

155
00:16:41.042 --> 00:16:42.876
- How?
- Survivor!

156
00:16:46.965 --> 00:16:48.924
Put him down.

157
00:16:48.925 --> 00:16:50.009
Gently.

158
00:16:50.593 --> 00:16:52.136
He's been through enough.

159
00:16:52.137 --> 00:16:55.807
Boy. this is your prince.
the son of King Saul.

160
00:16:56.474 --> 00:16:58.393
Speak only the truth. all right?

161
00:17:04.816 --> 00:17:06.192
My name is Jonathan.

162
00:17:07.360 --> 00:17:08.361
What is yours?

163
00:17:12.031 --> 00:17:13.283
Can you tell me who did this?

164
00:17:13.908 --> 00:17:15.118
Lord.

165
00:17:24.919 --> 00:17:26.336
Run!

166
00:17:26.337 --> 00:17:28.089
- Run!
- Run!

167
00:17:34.846 --> 00:17:37.556
Abba! Abba! Abba!

168
00:17:37.557 --> 00:17:39.100
- Run.
- Abba!

169
00:18:01.956 --> 00:18:03.333
I am so sorry.

170
00:18:06.669 --> 00:18:08.838
I'm your prince and I
failed to protect you.

171
00:18:10.882 --> 00:18:12.175
It's my job to protect you.

172
00:18:13.718 --> 00:18:15.720
Now. I need you to
tell me who did this.

173
00:18:17.096 --> 00:18:23.102
And I swear I will find them and
I will return them to the dust.

174
00:18:25.104 --> 00:18:26.105
Only for you.

175
00:19:01.099 --> 00:19:03.351
There were giants on
the earth in those days.

176
00:19:05.395 --> 00:19:06.855
And also after.

177
00:19:25.206 --> 00:19:26.875
You're
getting very good.

178
00:19:29.168 --> 00:19:30.961
Uh. all the sheep
are accounted for.

179
00:19:30.962 --> 00:19:31.963
Just as you asked.

180
00:19:32.714 --> 00:19:34.591
I did not come to see the flock.

181
00:19:37.594 --> 00:19:39.512
I apologize for last night.

182
00:19:40.597 --> 00:19:42.015
How I spoke to you.

183
00:19:45.143 --> 00:19:48.313
Your spirit is hers.

184
00:19:48.855 --> 00:19:51.315
A horse that can
never be bridled.

185
00:19:51.316 --> 00:19:53.025
Father. why do you
keep me in the hills?

186
00:19:53.026 --> 00:19:55.819
- You hide me away like a leper.
- David.

187
00:19:55.820 --> 00:19:57.279
Why not send me to
the king's army?

188
00:19:57.280 --> 00:19:58.405
Let me prove myself.

189
00:19:58.406 --> 00:20:01.617
There is no glory to be
earned by serving that king.

190
00:20:01.618 --> 00:20:04.578
- Tell that to Eliab.
- I have. Many times.

191
00:20:04.579 --> 00:20:08.498
So. why do my brothers get
to fight and I'm stuck here?

192
00:20:08.499 --> 00:20:10.084
Because he took them.

193
00:20:11.294 --> 00:20:14.922
And he takes our taxes and our
lands. just as the seer warned.

194
00:20:14.923 --> 00:20:17.050
Israel should never
have had a king.

195
00:20:17.550 --> 00:20:19.384
He has taken enough.

196
00:20:19.385 --> 00:20:21.470
I am not going to
let him take you.

197
00:20:21.471 --> 00:20:23.180
I don't belong here. Father.

198
00:20:23.181 --> 00:20:24.474
I know I do not.

199
00:20:26.225 --> 00:20:27.727
I was meant for more than this.

200
00:20:29.228 --> 00:20:30.938
How do you know that. David?

201
00:20:30.939 --> 00:20:33.191
Because God speaks to me.

202
00:20:33.775 --> 00:20:38.363
When I'm alone in the hills. I
hear his voice like Mother did.

203
00:20:39.072 --> 00:20:40.072
He tells me...

204
00:20:41.157 --> 00:20:42.282
Avva.

205
00:20:50.291 --> 00:20:51.292
Avva!

206
00:20:58.716 --> 00:20:59.717
Avva!

207
00:21:03.054 --> 00:21:04.764
Oh. no. Avva?

208
00:21:05.723 --> 00:21:07.433
David.

209
00:21:13.272 --> 00:21:14.357
Come here.

210
00:21:16.275 --> 00:21:17.694
You all right?

211
00:22:15.376 --> 00:22:18.004
Why
does God judge me?

212
00:22:18.671 --> 00:22:21.007
This demon attacks my home.

213
00:22:22.300 --> 00:22:23.301
David. stop.

214
00:22:24.218 --> 00:22:25.594
You cannot face it alone.

215
00:22:25.595 --> 00:22:27.555
I can and I will.

216
00:22:28.723 --> 00:22:30.850
- For all of us.
- No. wait.

217
00:22:31.684 --> 00:22:32.810
Wait.

218
00:22:33.978 --> 00:22:35.479
I am done waiting.

219
00:22:35.480 --> 00:22:37.065
David. wait!

220
00:22:59.796 --> 00:23:01.296
{\an8}What about the boy?

221
00:23:01.297 --> 00:23:02.715
{\an8}He'll stay with me.

222
00:23:04.759 --> 00:23:07.637
My prince. children tell tales.

223
00:23:08.304 --> 00:23:09.930
Nothing spreads like fear.

224
00:23:09.931 --> 00:23:11.223
And this boy...

225
00:23:11.224 --> 00:23:12.767
Hasn't spoken a word.

226
00:23:14.352 --> 00:23:15.353
Go.

227
00:23:15.895 --> 00:23:17.270
Be with your men.

228
00:23:17.271 --> 00:23:18.481
Enjoy your victory.

229
00:23:25.321 --> 00:23:30.992
Bless Gibeah! Bless the
house of Saul. son of Kish.

230
00:23:30.993 --> 00:23:33.453
pride of Benjamin.

231
00:23:33.454 --> 00:23:39.043
who fills our bellies with
the wine of Agag!

232
00:24:05.194 --> 00:24:07.904
Be sure the
king's throne is raised from the ground

233
00:24:07.905 --> 00:24:09.072
a half cubit.

234
00:24:09.073 --> 00:24:10.824
Honestly. Mother.
what does it matter?

235
00:24:10.825 --> 00:24:12.535
Every detail matters.

236
00:24:13.161 --> 00:24:15.245
Mychal. put it in.

237
00:24:15.246 --> 00:24:17.373
Your work is meaningful. Sedan.

238
00:24:18.207 --> 00:24:20.083
If only we had
you on the battlefield.

239
00:24:20.084 --> 00:24:21.543
We would have won the first day.

240
00:24:21.544 --> 00:24:23.086
- Jonathan.
- My queen.

241
00:24:23.087 --> 00:24:25.506
The Lord has
returned my son to me.

242
00:24:26.632 --> 00:24:29.801
No injuries?

243
00:24:29.802 --> 00:24:31.429
Not a scratch.

244
00:24:32.138 --> 00:24:33.472
Well. not many.

245
00:24:35.057 --> 00:24:36.100
Jonathan!

246
00:24:36.767 --> 00:24:39.186
- I prayed every day.
- Sister.

247
00:24:39.187 --> 00:24:41.897
- And who's this?
- Jonathan. you cannot save every stray.

248
00:24:41.898 --> 00:24:43.064
I could save this one.

249
00:24:43.065 --> 00:24:44.399
What
happened to him?

250
00:24:44.400 --> 00:24:48.111
His entire village was destroyed on
the border. He's the only survivor.

251
00:24:48.112 --> 00:24:50.530
Mychal. those silks
are from Egypt.

252
00:24:50.531 --> 00:24:51.489
Mother.

253
00:24:51.490 --> 00:24:52.866
The silks.

254
00:24:52.867 --> 00:24:53.909
What is your name?

255
00:24:53.910 --> 00:24:55.036
Doesn't speak.

256
00:24:56.537 --> 00:24:57.537
Reuben.

257
00:24:58.915 --> 00:25:01.333
Hello. Reuben. Come.

258
00:25:01.334 --> 00:25:02.751
Do you like figs?

259
00:25:02.752 --> 00:25:04.377
I love figs.

260
00:25:04.378 --> 00:25:05.462
How was the journey?

261
00:25:05.463 --> 00:25:07.339
Enough to make me vomit.

262
00:25:07.340 --> 00:25:11.177
Palace games must be dull
indeed if you seek a battlefield.

263
00:25:11.928 --> 00:25:14.554
The perils of the palace
dwarf the perils of the field.

264
00:25:14.555 --> 00:25:16.306
At least here you know
who your enemies are.

265
00:25:16.307 --> 00:25:17.516
Oh. not always.

266
00:25:18.267 --> 00:25:20.685
- Why have you come?
- Father summoned us.

267
00:25:20.686 --> 00:25:22.438
We are here to show unity.

268
00:25:23.105 --> 00:25:26.358
The tribes must be honored
and battles have heroes.

269
00:25:26.359 --> 00:25:28.110
And heroes need brides.

270
00:25:28.945 --> 00:25:30.404
As do princes.

271
00:25:36.911 --> 00:25:39.163
- You have grieved long enough.
- Mother.

272
00:25:39.872 --> 00:25:40.998
I just won a battle.

273
00:25:41.666 --> 00:25:43.334
I do not wish to fight another.

274
00:25:45.127 --> 00:25:47.504
- Where is Father?
- Up on a mountain somewhere.

275
00:25:47.505 --> 00:25:48.631
That one.

276
00:25:49.257 --> 00:25:51.424
Setting up
a victory monument.

277
00:25:51.425 --> 00:25:52.509
And Eshbaal?

278
00:25:52.510 --> 00:25:54.990
Surely you will find
him if you follow the plunder.

279
00:26:00.434 --> 00:26:02.937
- How else might I serve you. my prince?
- Hmm.

280
00:26:03.521 --> 00:26:06.941
Well. my cup is full for
now but. uh. stay close.

281
00:26:07.692 --> 00:26:10.653
Appetites replenish quickly.

282
00:26:15.741 --> 00:26:17.576
I have never been
so near royalty.

283
00:26:18.411 --> 00:26:20.620
Come.

284
00:26:20.621 --> 00:26:21.706
Sit.

285
00:26:24.417 --> 00:26:26.711
Sit. I don't bite.

286
00:26:28.337 --> 00:26:30.339
Here.

287
00:26:34.093 --> 00:26:36.846
You have such a beautiful face.

288
00:26:37.596 --> 00:26:38.889
Tell me...

289
00:26:39.932 --> 00:26:40.933
what is your name?

290
00:26:42.018 --> 00:26:44.477
Kezia.

291
00:26:44.478 --> 00:26:48.232
If I were to be assigned
to your sister's care...

292
00:26:49.233 --> 00:26:52.610
mmm. you would see
much more of me.

293
00:26:52.611 --> 00:26:56.698
Clever girl. aren't you?

294
00:26:56.699 --> 00:26:58.492
Perhaps I could. um.

295
00:26:59.744 --> 00:27:01.078
have that arranged.

296
00:27:01.787 --> 00:27:03.581
Will you be king one day?

297
00:27:06.459 --> 00:27:08.418
I. um...

298
00:27:08.419 --> 00:27:10.712
I much prefer the...

299
00:27:10.713 --> 00:27:14.133
...decadence of power to
the burden of the crown.

300
00:27:14.884 --> 00:27:17.260
- Eshbaal.
- Oh. speaking of burdens.

301
00:27:17.261 --> 00:27:18.763
Lord prince.

302
00:27:22.725 --> 00:27:23.885
Greetings. brother.

303
00:27:24.393 --> 00:27:26.978
You seem distressed.

304
00:27:26.979 --> 00:27:28.021
Did I miss an engagement?

305
00:27:28.022 --> 00:27:29.273
You know too well.

306
00:27:30.066 --> 00:27:31.107
You missed a great battle.

307
00:27:31.108 --> 00:27:33.985
Did I? Battle.

308
00:27:33.986 --> 00:27:37.906
The battle was fought and won by men
with a hunger for blood and conquest.

309
00:27:37.907 --> 00:27:38.990
You had no need of me.

310
00:27:38.991 --> 00:27:41.951
I'm far too young and
cultured for that drama.

311
00:27:41.952 --> 00:27:44.371
Men younger than you fought
and died in that battle.

312
00:27:44.372 --> 00:27:45.872
Good for them.

313
00:27:45.873 --> 00:27:47.792
May God reward their sacrifices.

314
00:27:51.587 --> 00:27:52.545
This was your doing.

315
00:27:52.546 --> 00:27:55.340
Brother. be more specific. I...

316
00:27:55.341 --> 00:27:58.594
You convinced Father to
keep these cursed objects.

317
00:28:00.763 --> 00:28:02.056
Cursed.

318
00:28:03.057 --> 00:28:05.768
They're quite shiny. don't
you think? To be cursed.

319
00:28:06.352 --> 00:28:09.688
Anyway. the king did not
raise any objections so...

320
00:28:11.440 --> 00:28:14.026
Come now. brother.

321
00:28:16.404 --> 00:28:17.905
Revel in our great victory.

322
00:28:20.658 --> 00:28:22.076
It's what you deserve.

323
00:28:28.207 --> 00:28:30.376
Okay.

324
00:28:31.419 --> 00:28:32.669
Suit yourself.

325
00:28:32.670 --> 00:28:34.003
My prince.

326
00:28:34.004 --> 00:28:36.298
Joab and Lord Abner request you.

327
00:28:39.093 --> 00:28:40.094
Run along.

328
00:28:41.053 --> 00:28:42.554
We will speak of this again.

329
00:28:42.555 --> 00:28:43.806
Well. I can't wait.

330
00:28:49.562 --> 00:28:52.564
I can portion you
50 oxen and 400 sheep.

331
00:28:52.565 --> 00:28:55.358
Why should we be least
among the houses of Israel?

332
00:28:55.359 --> 00:28:56.651
Because you are.

333
00:28:56.652 --> 00:28:57.610
Now go.

334
00:28:57.611 --> 00:29:01.573
Abner. double their portion.

335
00:29:01.574 --> 00:29:03.492
You are not least in my eyes.

336
00:29:04.201 --> 00:29:05.953
May the
king live forever.

337
00:29:07.496 --> 00:29:09.539
You give too much.

338
00:29:09.540 --> 00:29:10.623
I am generous.

339
00:29:10.624 --> 00:29:14.002
Loyalty achieved through
commerce is fleeting.

340
00:29:14.003 --> 00:29:19.091
As is youth. But it delights
while it lasts. my old friend.

341
00:29:37.359 --> 00:29:38.485
Father.

342
00:29:38.486 --> 00:29:40.403
Jonathan. My son.

343
00:29:40.404 --> 00:29:41.489
My king.

344
00:29:45.951 --> 00:29:47.327
Quite the stele. no?

345
00:29:47.328 --> 00:29:48.995
And what a great honor.

346
00:29:48.996 --> 00:29:50.371
Defeat of the Amalekites.

347
00:29:50.372 --> 00:29:51.498
More than that.

348
00:29:51.499 --> 00:29:54.167
It will be a
memorial of all time.

349
00:29:54.168 --> 00:29:56.127
To the greatness of our house.

350
00:29:56.128 --> 00:29:57.796
The glory of Israel.

351
00:29:58.547 --> 00:29:59.757
Greatness of God.

352
00:30:00.257 --> 00:30:02.510
Our greatness is his greatness.

353
00:30:05.763 --> 00:30:07.223
What of the border village?

354
00:30:07.973 --> 00:30:09.266
Completely destroyed.

355
00:30:09.767 --> 00:30:11.184
- Hmm.
- One survivor.

356
00:30:11.185 --> 00:30:15.063
- A child. Brought him here.
- Destroyed by whom?

357
00:30:15.064 --> 00:30:16.147
Unknown.

358
00:30:16.148 --> 00:30:20.069
Except I saw the print of a hand
larger than a weaver's basket.

359
00:30:21.028 --> 00:30:22.947
And arrows the size of spears.

360
00:30:25.324 --> 00:30:28.953
Giants have not roamed these
lands since the days of Joshua.

361
00:30:29.453 --> 00:30:31.372
Not for hundreds of years.

362
00:30:33.040 --> 00:30:36.042
This is a Philistine
trick to intimidate us.

363
00:30:36.043 --> 00:30:38.254
To terrify us back into caves.

364
00:30:39.463 --> 00:30:40.506
Let us hope.

365
00:30:41.674 --> 00:30:43.759
You are still troubled?

366
00:30:45.928 --> 00:30:48.514
Why are we dividing the
spoils of the blood drinkers?

367
00:30:49.807 --> 00:30:51.058
Slaving their people?

368
00:30:52.226 --> 00:30:53.561
We're told to keep nothing.

369
00:30:55.062 --> 00:30:56.229
By Samuel.

370
00:30:56.230 --> 00:30:57.856
Yes. Father. By Samuel.

371
00:30:59.692 --> 00:31:00.693
Yes.

372
00:31:01.443 --> 00:31:04.321
Son. his time has passed.

373
00:31:05.948 --> 00:31:07.991
The age of judges is over.

374
00:31:07.992 --> 00:31:12.495
This is the age of kings
and we are its stewards.

375
00:31:12.496 --> 00:31:14.915
The first dynasty of Israel.

376
00:31:16.125 --> 00:31:17.543
Well. we should still honor him.

377
00:31:18.252 --> 00:31:19.378
He speaks for God.

378
00:31:20.629 --> 00:31:22.797
Why can God not speak to me?

379
00:31:22.798 --> 00:31:24.049
His anointed.

380
00:31:24.842 --> 00:31:26.427
Anointed by Samuel.

381
00:31:30.639 --> 00:31:32.808
Jonathan.

382
00:31:34.310 --> 00:31:38.438
When you are king someone
will always be angry with you.

383
00:31:38.439 --> 00:31:39.523
Always.

384
00:31:40.941 --> 00:31:42.568
So who should I appease?

385
00:31:43.277 --> 00:31:46.697
The leaders of the 12 tribes.
men who fought for us.

386
00:31:47.197 --> 00:31:49.825
died in service of our throne?

387
00:31:50.659 --> 00:31:51.784
Or one man?

388
00:31:54.747 --> 00:31:56.289
I have no love for
these politics.

389
00:31:56.290 --> 00:31:58.542
Life is politics. son.

390
00:31:59.460 --> 00:32:01.462
Even more so on the throne.

391
00:32:02.671 --> 00:32:03.797
Even now.

392
00:32:04.757 --> 00:32:05.758
Come.

393
00:32:06.300 --> 00:32:08.218
We have a celebration to enjoy.

394
00:32:20.731 --> 00:32:22.399
Oh. Saul...

395
00:32:26.070 --> 00:32:27.112
My son...

396
00:32:28.614 --> 00:32:30.574
What have you done?

397
00:32:34.536 --> 00:32:36.163
What have you done?

398
00:32:41.085 --> 00:32:42.795
Does the Lord speak?

399
00:32:43.587 --> 00:32:44.838
We must go.

400
00:32:49.218 --> 00:32:50.219
Where?

401
00:32:53.847 --> 00:32:56.892
To speak the words
that were spoken to me.

402
00:32:58.811 --> 00:33:01.980
To unmake what has been made.

403
00:33:03.816 --> 00:33:05.943
Master. wait. your shoes.

404
00:33:19.873 --> 00:33:24.753
Look at all the joy and prosperity
you have brought our people.

405
00:33:29.717 --> 00:33:31.343
Enjoy it.

406
00:33:41.145 --> 00:33:42.229
The king!

407
00:34:06.336 --> 00:34:07.421
Sorry.

408
00:34:09.923 --> 00:34:12.259
Here. Take some of that.

409
00:34:13.969 --> 00:34:16.053
- Yes. Mother?
- Behave.

410
00:34:16.054 --> 00:34:17.054
When do I not?

411
00:34:17.055 --> 00:34:20.516
You
have your own wine.

412
00:34:20.517 --> 00:34:22.837
They save the
best wine for the king's table.

413
00:34:23.937 --> 00:34:24.937
But that's... No...

414
00:34:24.938 --> 00:34:27.357
Then you should stay
at the king's table.

415
00:34:28.317 --> 00:34:29.610
Please.

416
00:34:30.486 --> 00:34:34.448
Please. please. please. please.

417
00:34:35.616 --> 00:34:36.742
Please.

418
00:34:37.284 --> 00:34:40.661
Sons. My king. my king.

419
00:34:40.662 --> 00:34:42.163
Lord of all Israel.

420
00:34:42.164 --> 00:34:44.457
I am Adriel. son of Barzillai.

421
00:34:44.458 --> 00:34:46.501
Elder of the tribe of Judah.

422
00:34:46.502 --> 00:34:49.254
Greetings. Adriel.
son of Barzillai.

423
00:34:50.005 --> 00:34:53.549
Judah has long been a lion
among the sons of Abraham.

424
00:34:53.550 --> 00:34:56.511
Just as Benjamin has
produced a great light in you

425
00:34:56.512 --> 00:34:59.348
for such a small tribe.

426
00:35:00.015 --> 00:35:04.435
The greatest has
come from the least. huh?

427
00:35:06.563 --> 00:35:09.357
When I was young
we were scattered.

428
00:35:09.358 --> 00:35:13.903
hiding in caves from the
enemies you have now conquered.

429
00:35:13.904 --> 00:35:18.242
Leaderless. divided. preyed upon
by every neighboring nation.

430
00:35:18.826 --> 00:35:25.581
But the Lord of hosts heard our
cry and blessed us with a king.

431
00:35:25.582 --> 00:35:29.794
Saul. son of Kish. of
the tribe of Benjamin.

432
00:35:29.795 --> 00:35:33.256
And you. Saul. have
made us a nation.

433
00:35:33.257 --> 00:35:35.466
You have made us feared.

434
00:35:35.467 --> 00:35:39.930
You have made us wealthy with
the spoils of the Amalekites.

435
00:35:41.098 --> 00:35:44.309
We now feast on their
cattle and drink their wine.

436
00:35:44.810 --> 00:35:50.481
And their mighty King Agag sits
humiliated at your feet.

437
00:35:50.482 --> 00:35:55.779
So the tribe of Judah renews its
pledge of fealty to the anointed

438
00:35:56.405 --> 00:36:02.201
of the Lord Most High. to the
house of Saul. king of all Israel.

439
00:36:02.202 --> 00:36:06.790
May your reign endure
for all generations.

440
00:36:15.757 --> 00:36:21.179
I thank Judah for their loyalty
and raise this cup not for myself.

441
00:36:22.681 --> 00:36:23.849
but I raise it

442
00:36:25.559 --> 00:36:26.559
for my son

443
00:36:26.560 --> 00:36:30.647
whose courage and conviction
go before him always.

444
00:36:31.356 --> 00:36:34.275
Whose heart is steadfast.

445
00:36:34.276 --> 00:36:37.695
I pray I am remembered
as a good king.

446
00:36:37.696 --> 00:36:40.240
but he will be greater than I.

447
00:36:41.074 --> 00:36:45.912
To your prince and
my beloved son.

448
00:36:45.913 --> 00:36:50.416
To Jonathan and
his coming reign.

449
00:36:50.417 --> 00:36:53.378
To Jonathan. my beloved brother.

450
00:36:54.046 --> 00:36:55.923
Perfect in every way.

451
00:37:00.093 --> 00:37:01.510
To the house of Saul.

452
00:37:47.474 --> 00:37:52.979
Who can stand against the hero of
Issachar and claim the sword of Agag?

453
00:37:52.980 --> 00:37:56.108
Eliab. Come. fight for
the tribe of Judah!

454
00:37:57.985 --> 00:38:00.736
Who will take a bet
on Eliab of Judah?

455
00:38:05.951 --> 00:38:06.952
My lord.

456
00:38:08.537 --> 00:38:10.205
Why does the witch king live?

457
00:38:13.709 --> 00:38:17.170
I will not gift him death
without humiliation.

458
00:38:19.047 --> 00:38:21.924
He has tormented our
people for a generation.

459
00:38:21.925 --> 00:38:25.554
His kind have cannibals
and sorcerers.

460
00:38:26.847 --> 00:38:28.222
He does not belong here.

461
00:38:28.223 --> 00:38:32.936
He's exactly where he belongs.
Beneath my feet. Powerless.

462
00:38:33.687 --> 00:38:35.646
His presence here.
believe me when I say...

463
00:38:35.647 --> 00:38:37.941
I think you need wine.

464
00:38:39.443 --> 00:38:40.610
Relax.

465
00:38:41.737 --> 00:38:43.071
Place a wager.

466
00:39:28.408 --> 00:39:32.162
Your time
is done. blood drinker.

467
00:39:33.455 --> 00:39:35.832
Is it?

468
00:39:51.640 --> 00:39:53.016
Fear is the enemy.

469
00:39:54.309 --> 00:39:55.602
Fear is the thief.

470
00:39:59.773 --> 00:40:02.275
Lion!

471
00:40:50.031 --> 00:40:56.287
On the hill above this feast
I found a stele which reads.

472
00:40:56.288 --> 00:41:02.919
"To the glory of the house of Saul.
he has defeated the Amalekites.

473
00:41:04.379 --> 00:41:06.798
May his fame reach every sea.

474
00:41:08.133 --> 00:41:11.428
May his throne endure
for all generations.

475
00:41:14.848 --> 00:41:16.850
To the glory of Saul..."

476
00:41:20.145 --> 00:41:21.938
The glory of Saul.

477
00:41:24.274 --> 00:41:27.861
We have a prophet of the
Most High God in our midst.

478
00:41:28.445 --> 00:41:31.698
Greetings. Samuel.
son of Elkanah.

479
00:41:32.365 --> 00:41:36.076
Blessed are you. seer
of the Lord of hosts.

480
00:41:36.077 --> 00:41:40.039
Greetings. Saul. son of Kish.
of the tribe of Benjamin.

481
00:41:40.040 --> 00:41:44.335
The least of the tribes of
Israel has produced a great line.

482
00:41:44.336 --> 00:41:47.088
Have you come to sacrifice with us?

483
00:41:47.589 --> 00:41:50.925
To consecrate this victory
and this day with us?

484
00:41:50.926 --> 00:41:53.260
I've come to speak the
words of the Lord God

485
00:41:53.261 --> 00:41:55.430
spoken to me last night.

486
00:41:59.100 --> 00:42:02.187
We have obeyed the
commands of the Lord.

487
00:42:05.315 --> 00:42:08.192
The Amalekites have
been utterly destroyed.

488
00:42:12.405 --> 00:42:13.573
Is it so?

489
00:42:16.451 --> 00:42:19.537
Then why is the bleating
of sheep in my ears? Hmm?

490
00:42:20.497 --> 00:42:22.374
Why the lowing of cattle?

491
00:42:23.917 --> 00:42:24.918
Huh?

492
00:42:33.176 --> 00:42:37.514
Why has filth been brought in to
pollute what is meant to be holy?

493
00:42:43.103 --> 00:42:44.104
Come.

494
00:42:44.980 --> 00:42:46.397
Come. my old friend.

495
00:42:46.398 --> 00:42:48.066
Tonight we celebrate.

496
00:42:49.776 --> 00:42:51.361
We tell the old stories.

497
00:42:52.362 --> 00:42:54.656
We remember the
greatness of God.

498
00:42:55.573 --> 00:42:56.574
Come.

499
00:43:01.121 --> 00:43:02.914
Speak with me alone.

500
00:43:42.495 --> 00:43:44.080
Save the sacrifice.

501
00:43:44.914 --> 00:43:48.125
We have sacrificed thousands
of men on the field.

502
00:43:48.126 --> 00:43:49.586
Is that not enough?

503
00:43:51.046 --> 00:43:54.591
Now you come and shame me in
front of the tribes of Israel.

504
00:43:55.342 --> 00:43:56.842
You scold me like a boy.

505
00:43:56.843 --> 00:43:58.845
I anointed a boy.

506
00:43:59.387 --> 00:44:01.597
Humble in his own eyes.

507
00:44:01.598 --> 00:44:05.309
As king. I am what you made me.

508
00:44:05.310 --> 00:44:06.727
I wept for you. Saul.

509
00:44:06.728 --> 00:44:09.439
In rage and tears all night.

510
00:44:11.024 --> 00:44:15.986
I pleaded with the Lord of all
Heaven but he would not relent.

511
00:44:15.987 --> 00:44:18.989
Now I must speak
as he has spoken.

512
00:44:18.990 --> 00:44:21.076
Convenient. is it not?

513
00:44:21.785 --> 00:44:25.789
How am I to know the difference
between the words of the Most High

514
00:44:26.581 --> 00:44:30.085
and the rumblings of
a jealous old man?

515
00:44:33.713 --> 00:44:35.298
I loved you like a son.

516
00:44:36.049 --> 00:44:38.635
And yet. your sons
did not love you.

517
00:44:41.638 --> 00:44:43.680
They did not follow
in your ways.

518
00:44:43.681 --> 00:44:46.058
Is that not why the
people demanded a king?

519
00:44:46.059 --> 00:44:47.310
All right. Saul.

520
00:44:49.187 --> 00:44:52.565
I will tell you what the Lord
God of Israel has said to me.

521
00:44:54.859 --> 00:44:56.069
Speak.

522
00:44:58.863 --> 00:45:01.074
"I regret I made Saul king.

523
00:45:02.075 --> 00:45:03.868
He has turned his back on me

524
00:45:05.078 --> 00:45:07.371
and has not followed
my command."

525
00:45:41.156 --> 00:45:42.240
Mychal.

526
00:45:44.200 --> 00:45:45.743
What have we done?

527
00:45:46.369 --> 00:45:48.787
I obeyed the voice of the Lord.

528
00:45:48.788 --> 00:45:51.457
I utterly destroyed
the Amalekites.

529
00:45:51.458 --> 00:45:53.167
Yet Agag lives.

530
00:45:53.168 --> 00:45:55.461
Chained beneath my
table like a dog.

531
00:45:55.462 --> 00:45:58.089
You were told to slay him.

532
00:46:00.467 --> 00:46:04.637
I built a kingdom from
nothing. from scattered tribes.

533
00:46:06.139 --> 00:46:08.223
Why is this not enough?

534
00:46:08.224 --> 00:46:11.853
You built a kingdom?

535
00:46:13.146 --> 00:46:14.147
You?

536
00:46:20.987 --> 00:46:26.533
Saul. when you were small in your own eyes
the Lord lifted you up and made you king.

537
00:46:26.534 --> 00:46:32.122
Now that you are great in your
own eyes you have rebelled

538
00:46:32.123 --> 00:46:35.876
and made yourself even
in the eyes of the Lord.

539
00:46:35.877 --> 00:46:37.419
Even?

540
00:46:37.420 --> 00:46:41.757
You have twisted the throne
of Israel to your own glory

541
00:46:41.758 --> 00:46:47.972
so you will be given to a twisted
power and your own torment.

542
00:46:48.598 --> 00:46:51.141
Your mind will be cursed.

543
00:46:51.142 --> 00:46:53.060
Get out of my head. sorcerer.

544
00:46:53.061 --> 00:46:55.063
I am no sorcerer.

545
00:46:58.650 --> 00:47:00.860
I am a messenger only.

546
00:47:01.986 --> 00:47:03.363
Samuel.

547
00:47:04.697 --> 00:47:06.658
I was afraid of the people.

548
00:47:09.077 --> 00:47:11.788
I kept back the
best to sacrifice.

549
00:47:13.456 --> 00:47:15.290
I-I would sacrifice them all.

550
00:47:15.291 --> 00:47:19.002
To obey is better
than sacrifice.

551
00:47:19.003 --> 00:47:22.549
to heed better than
the fat of the rams.

552
00:47:23.299 --> 00:47:27.052
Rebellion is as the
sin of witchcraft.

553
00:47:27.053 --> 00:47:31.056
stubbornness is as
inequity and idolatry.

554
00:47:31.057 --> 00:47:32.724
I was afraid of them.

555
00:47:32.725 --> 00:47:36.186
Why? Why would you be
afraid of the people?

556
00:47:36.187 --> 00:47:39.816
Why are you not afraid
of God instead of man?

557
00:47:42.277 --> 00:47:45.530
I loved you.

558
00:47:53.663 --> 00:47:55.206
I anointed you.

559
00:47:59.669 --> 00:48:00.753
Bless me.

560
00:48:02.380 --> 00:48:04.090
Sacrifice with me.

561
00:48:04.924 --> 00:48:07.551
You chose me as a king.
You are a father to me.

562
00:48:07.552 --> 00:48:09.261
God chose you.

563
00:48:09.262 --> 00:48:11.513
Now he chooses another

564
00:48:11.514 --> 00:48:14.808
because you have rejected the
word of the Lord your God.

565
00:48:14.809 --> 00:48:19.731
so the Lord your God
now rejects you as king.

566
00:48:21.899 --> 00:48:24.235
His spirit is
withdrawn from you.

567
00:48:26.362 --> 00:48:30.742
This is my kingdom
and my son's after me.

568
00:48:31.409 --> 00:48:32.619
Jonathan will rule.

569
00:48:33.328 --> 00:48:34.703
He will never rule.

570
00:48:34.704 --> 00:48:36.456
Samuel.

571
00:48:42.003 --> 00:48:48.551
The Lord has torn a kingdom from
you and given it to one greater than you.

572
00:48:49.052 --> 00:48:50.261
Who is he?

573
00:48:57.560 --> 00:48:58.561
Samuel?

574
00:49:01.773 --> 00:49:03.107
Samuel?

575
00:49:05.234 --> 00:49:07.445
Samuel!

576
00:49:09.197 --> 00:49:11.449
Samuel!

577
00:49:19.707 --> 00:49:21.375
I'm sorry. my child.

578
00:49:21.376 --> 00:49:24.378
Samuel!

579
00:49:24.379 --> 00:49:25.545
Father. what happened?

580
00:49:25.546 --> 00:49:28.131
- Samuel!
- Father. What happened?

581
00:49:28.132 --> 00:49:29.508
Get away from me!

582
00:49:29.509 --> 00:49:32.386
Get away!

583
00:49:39.227 --> 00:49:40.644
Samuel.

584
00:49:44.857 --> 00:49:46.234
Father.

585
00:49:49.153 --> 00:49:50.363
Help!

586
00:49:52.073 --> 00:49:53.282
Help me!

587
00:50:34.365 --> 00:50:36.868
I'm tired of being afraid.

588
00:50:40.037 --> 00:50:44.083
God said to Joshua. "Be
strong and courageous.

589
00:50:45.835 --> 00:50:47.170
Do not fear."

590
00:51:15.865 --> 00:51:20.369
Why have the
gods come to this place?

591
00:51:20.995 --> 00:51:23.121
The God of gods has come.

592
00:51:23.122 --> 00:51:30.171
Surely
the wrath of Saul has passed.

593
00:51:33.424 --> 00:51:36.469
The wrath of Saul has passed.

594
00:51:38.554 --> 00:51:41.599
But the wrath of God has not.

595
00:51:47.897 --> 00:51:51.316
As your sword has
made women childless.

596
00:51:51.317 --> 00:51:57.365
so shall your mother be
childless for all time.

597
00:52:39.282 --> 00:52:42.910
God is not mocked.

598
00:53:25.786 --> 00:53:29.206
Master. where are we going now?

599
00:53:34.754 --> 00:53:36.505
To find a king.

600
00:54:05.534 --> 00:54:09.371
<i>So can one stone
change the course of history?</i>

601
00:54:12.917 --> 00:54:15.252
<i>Yes. it can.</i>

602
00:54:16.587 --> 00:54:18.756
<i>But destiny comes at a cost.</i>

603
00:54:19.757 --> 00:54:25.136
<i>And the rise of David would
cost my family everything.</i>

603
00:54:26.305 --> 00:55:26.173
